edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.operators

Class IconOperators

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.operators.IconOperators

  • public class IconOperators
extends Object
    Defines many of the Unicon operators. For efficiency, each operator is a static field that implements IIconOperator. The Junicon Spring configuration file then correlates operator symbols to these static fields using its OperatorOverAtoms property.

    For operators as well as an iterator's nextAtom(), there is no difference in behavior between null and an atom that holds null, and null is not treated as failure.

    Note that IconNumber.toNumber() returns null if input is not number or null.

      • sameNumberAs

        public static BinaryOperator<IIconAtom> sameNumberAs
        x=y Test for numeric equality. Convert both to numbers if either is a number or a number in string form. It is an error if one is a number and the other is not. SO: "1"="1.0", but 1="hello" gives an error.

      • sameStringAs

        public static BinaryOperator<IIconAtom> sameStringAs

      • sameValueAs

        public static BinaryOperator<IIconAtom> sameValueAs
        x===y Test for value equality. Tests if arguments are equal using equals(). Value comparison fails if x and y do not have the same type.

      • questionMarkUnary

        public static UnaryOperator<IIconAtom> questionMarkUnary
        x?y, ?x Random or string search operator. ?list gives an updatable index reference using a random position. ?collection or ?set gives a randomly selected value. ?string gives an index reference using a random position, which is updatable if the operand is a variable, and replaces the variable. ?map gives an updatable index reference using a random key. ?record or ?object gives an updatable reference to a random public field. ?integer gives a random integer j where 1<=j<=integer. ?0 gives a random real r where 0<=r<=1. string?operator gives results of string matching.

      • getChannel

        public static BlockingQueue getChannel(Object x,
                                       boolean isSend)
        Get channel from given co-expression or channel, or current co-expression if null. If channel is null, uses current co-expression: if isSend uses outbox, else uses inbox. If channel is a BlockingQueue, i.e., is a channel, just use it. Otherwise, channel is a co-expression: if isSend uses inbox, else uses outbox.
